Anti-apartheid struggle veteran Ahmed Kathrada is recovering well and in a stable condition after the removal of a blood clot on the brain two weeks ago.Ahmed Kathrada Foundation spokesperson Neeshan Balton said although his condition is stable he faces some challenges, such as vulnerability to infection, which makes his condition unpredictable.Kathrada was hospitalised on March 4 for surgery related to blood clotting on the brain. He remains hospitalised in Joburg, said Balton .This after rumours escalated about his death last week . We condemn these rumours and request the public to refrain from re-posting or spreading fake news or any updates that cannot be verified. We reiterate our commitment to providing regular and accurate updates about Mr Kathrada s condition both to the media and the public, said Balton Balton also thanked the public for the various initiatives that have been organised to wish Kathrada well. We are deeply grateful for the immense support from the public. We are thankful for the various prayer meetings, vigils and messages of support that continue pouring in,&#8221; he saidTNA Reporter